name: Kedai Menari
address: Pangkung Karung, Kerambitan, Tabanan Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: Despite its small size, the place offers delicious coffee and a variety of lunch options. There are some dishes worth trying, and they also serve beer and signature alcoholic drinks like ginseng arak. It's a great spot to check out if you're in the Kerambitan area.
review 2: Cute lovely mini restaurant with specialty: Sate Lilit. Ordered Ayam bakar (sweet and tasty), ayam goreng, nasi kulit. They also have promo for tower beer and live music on saturday. Worth to try.
review 3: The location is quite strategic. The place is tiny but homey with a simple industrial style. They served "nasi bejek" which is one of the local dishes in the Tabanan area with a very affordable price but presented in a modern way. Other menus are affordable too i.e satay lilit, coffee, snacks, etc. Recommended if you are passing this area.
